text.tspan: Future News is a media outlet of TAFFD (Transdisciplinary Agora for
Future Discussions) founded by Osinakachi Akuma Kalu, with William
Etete Daxon as CEO. I am Kingyin Yan, an AI researcher from Hong
Kong. I and some partners are proposing to build a public
commenting or discussion function to Future News, upholding the
following principles:
verifiable freedom of speech
objectivity and adherence to scientific truth guided by AI
openness and transparency to the public
likes = coins = voting power, building solidarity for political activism
meritocratic assignment of credits and
rewards using crypto coins according to DAO
(distirbutive autonomous organization)
principles, in particular that our team (or just a
limited sub-group within Future News) will be
operated democratically by weighted mutual
voting.
* The last point may be contentious as it may
disrupt the current management style of Future
News. But it has been the "vision" that I was
developing with Sujeet, Veer, and many others,
over many years.
We can discuss that and see if there's any way
that's acceptable by Future News.1
